# Cursor AI Rules for Moreach Project

## Documentation Rules
- NEVER proactively create documentation files (*.md) or README files
- Only create documentation files if explicitly requested by the user
- Keep documentation minimal and consolidated in existing files
- If documentation is needed, update existing files instead of creating new ones

## Code Rules
- Always respond in English
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Use the UI style shown in screenshots: card-based minimal design with icons
- Follow the existing project architecture and patterns

## Testing Rules
- NEVER include operational actions in TODO items (linting, testing, searching codebase)
- Only create TODOs for actual user-facing features or tasks

## File Creation Rules
- Ask before creating new configuration files
- Ask before creating new migration scripts
- Only create files that are strictly necessary for functionality

